## ⚡ ASYNC EXECUTION RULES

When making multiple independent AI calls, **DEFAULT TO PARALLEL** using `withTaskGroup`.

Only use sequential if:
- Order matters (output of call N is input to call N+1)
- Debugging requires predictable ordering

### ✅ CORRECT - Parallel (use this)

```swift
await withTaskGroup(of: ResultType?.self) { group in
    for item in items {
        group.addTask {
            try? await self.processItem(item)
        }
    }

    for await result in group {
        if let result = result {
            results.append(result)
        }
    }
}
```

### ❌ WRONG - Sequential (avoid unless order matters)

```swift
for item in items {
    let result = await processItem(item)  // SEQUENTIAL - 5x slower for 5 items
    results.append(result)
}
```

### Why This Matters

- 5 sequential API calls = 5x the wait time
- 5 parallel API calls = ~1x the wait time (all run concurrently)
- Fidelity tests, batch processing, multi-video analysis should ALL be parallel

